Most people think protein = muscle gains. But here’s the truth:
• 🧬 Protein builds every cell — skin, hair, organs, even your immune cells.
• 🧠 It powers your brain — neurotransmitters like serotonin are made from amino acids.
• 🛡️ It fuels your immune system — antibodies? Also proteins.
• 🍽️ It helps you stay full and manage weight.
• 🩹 And it’s critical for healing after injury or surgery.
Bottom line: protein keeps your entire body running — not just your biceps. 💪
👉 Don’t eat protein just for muscles — eat it for your life.
